Technical Problems
3. Technical Problems

There are a variety of technical objections to modal fictionalism, and
if these objections succeeded they would derail specific proposals
like that of Rosen 1990 and perhaps cause difficulties for modal
fictionalism in general. The most discussed of these objections is the
Brock/Rosen objection, an objection to the theory of Rosen 1990,
published independently in Brock 1993 and Rosen 1993. (In the case of
Rosen 1993, a variety was also leveled at the fictionalism of
Armstrong 1989).
